This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   - Investigate and document a browser bug where display-p3 colors in SVG background images get clamped to sRGB when `background-repeat` is used (Chrome & Safari)
   - Write a blog post about the bug
   - Build homepage features: word count display, divider graphic component, card hover effects
   - Create a shared/reusable `drawStrokes` function to DRY up duplicated SVG stroke generation logic, inlined via Eleventy's JS bundling (not an external file)
   - Session rule: do not write code unless explicitly told to (relaxed as session progressed and user started requesting code changes)

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - Display P3 / wide gamut color spaces in CSS and SVG
   - Browser SVG rasterization pipeline (intermediate sRGB buffer when tiling)
   - PNG ICC color profiles (cHRM/gAMA chunks) vs SVG color declarations
   - Eleventy/WebC component patterns: `webc:root="override"`, `webc:scoped`, `webc:keep`, `webc:bucket`
   - WebC `@text` uses JS function call syntax, not Nunjucks pipe syntax
   - `webc:keep` outputs script per component instance; `webc:bucket="components"` bundles once into layout
   - SVG filters: feTurbulence + feDisplacementMap for hand-drawn stroke effect
   - Adjacent sibling selector (`+`) broken by `<script>` tags between elements
   - Eleventy collections, filters, and `getBundle('js', 'components')`

3. Files and Code Sections:

   - **`src/blog/2026/display-p3-background-repeat-bug.md`**
     - Blog post about the P3 SVG background-repeat bug
     - Originally created at `src/blog/display-p3-background-repeat-bug.md`, moved to `2026/` subdirectory
     - Layout updated from `layouts/article.njk` to `layout-article.webc`
     - User heavily edited content, title, description after initial draft

   - **`eleventy.config.js`** — Added `totalWordCount` filter
     - Strips frontmatter (`rawInput` approach failed; uses rendered `content` via function call syntax)
     - Strips `<pre>` blocks and HTML tags, counts whitespace-separated words
     - Returns formatted string with `toLocaleString("en-US")`
     ```javascript
     conf.addFilter("totalWordCount", (posts) => {
       return posts.reduce((total, post) => {
         const raw = post.rawInput || "";
         const text = raw
           .replace(/^---[\s\S]*?---/, "")
           .replace(/```[\s\S]*?```/g, "")
           .replace(/<pre[\s>][\s\S]*?<\/pre>/gi, "")
           .replace(/<[^>]+>/g, "")
           .replace(/\s+/g, " ")
           .trim();
         return total + (text ? text.split(" ").length : 0);
       }, 0).toLocaleString("en-US");
     });
     ```

   - **`src/_components/home-contents-tertiary.webc`** — Blog/About callout cards on homepage
     ```html
